verify_stacked_die(25.10)                            verify_stacked_die(25.10)

Name
       verify_stacked_die - Checks die edge violation between adjacent dies

Syntax
       verify_stacked_die

       [-help]

       [-check_type <type_name>]

       [-chip_name {<chip1> <chip2> ...}]

       Checks die edge violation between adjacent dies. Once you define an OBS
       layer inside a macro, the adjacent die edge should not overlap this OBS
       area.  If  there  is  any  violation between macro OBS and adjacent die
       edge, it will be marked in the GUI window.

       This command must be used after readDieAbstract to input adjacent die's
       die abstract file.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description of the verify_stacked_die command us-
              age.

              For a detailed description of the command, use the man command:

              man verify_stacked_die

       -check_type <type_name>
              Specifies  the  check  constrain  types.  Currently,  only   the
              die_edge and bump_keepout zone checking are supported.

       -chip_name {<chip1> <chip2> ...}
              Specifies  the  name  of  the  adjacent chip whose edge is to be
              checked for violation. In a 3D-IC design, there  could  be  more
              than  one top die (in interposer design), so you can specify the
              chip that needs to be checked. Using  this  parameter,  you  can
              check one or more chips at the same time.

Examples
              * The  following  command  checks die edge violation between the
                macro's keep-out area and adjacent die mother_die:

                verify_stacked_die -chip_name {mother_die}

